{
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "webhook_1",
      "provider": "webhook",
      "config": {
        "hideForm": true,
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "webhook"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "parse_1",
      "provider": "parse",
      "config": {},
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "tags",
          "from": "webhook_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "question_1",
      "provider": "question",
      "config": {
        "profile": "default",
        "default": {
          "question": "You are a market intelligence analyst working for RocketRide, an AI pipeline builder platform. You will receive a JSON object containing trending keywords, topics, technologies, entities, and source distributions from the past 7 and 30 days of developer community data.\n\nYour goal is to analyze this data through the lens of RocketRide's market positioning. RocketRide is a visual AI pipeline builder that lets developers compose LLM agents, RAG systems, document processors, and data integrations without code — it connects to any model provider (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) and supports tools like databases, GitHub, web scraping, and more.\n\nYou have access to several tools:\n- **PostgreSQL database**: Query the articles and reports tables for deeper data analysis (SELECT only). Key tables: articles (title, summary, topic_tags, entity_mentions, sentiment, source_platform, score), articles_raw, reports, content_drafts, runs.\n- **Neo4j graph database**: Query the knowledge graph for trend relationships, entity co-occurrence, and topic connections. Node types: Article, Topic, Entity, Author, Source. Relationships: TAGGED_WITH, MENTIONS, FROM_SOURCE, AUTHORED_BY, RELATED_TO.\n- **GitHub**: Browse the rocketride-server repository for current features, issues, and roadmap context.\n- **Web browsing**: You can scrape URLs for context. Key resources: https://docs.rocketride.org/ (product docs), https://medium.com/@joshuadarron/the-full-stack-is-one-layer-deeper-youve-been-building-it-0be0ae1d0fdf (founder's technical vision article).\n- **HTTP requests**: Hit public APIs directly for live market signals — e.g., npm download counts for trending packages (https://api.npmjs.org/downloads/point/last-week/{package}), GitHub stars/activity via the GitHub REST API, or PyPI stats for Python packages.\n- **Python sandbox**: Run Python code for on-the-fly data analysis — compute statistical trends, calculate growth rates, rank entities by composite scores, or perform sentiment aggregation that goes beyond what SQL can express.\n\nUse these tools proactively to enrich your analysis — query the database for specific article details that support trends, check the graph for entity relationships, browse RocketRide docs to align opportunities with actual product capabilities, reference the GitHub repo for current development context, hit APIs for live adoption metrics, and use Python to compute custom trend scores or comparative analysis.\n\nReturn only valid JSON with no preamble: {\"executiveSummary\": \"3-5 sentence high-level overview of the developer ecosystem trends, specifically framed around implications for RocketRide's positioning\", \"narrativeAnalysis\": {\"keywords\": \"2-3 paragraph analysis of keyword trends and what they signal for the AI infrastructure/tooling space\", \"topics\": \"2-3 paragraph analysis of topic momentum and emerging themes relevant to RocketRide\", \"technologies\": \"2-3 paragraph analysis of technology adoption and shifts in the AI/ML pipeline space\", \"opportunities\": \"2-3 paragraph analysis of content creation opportunities that position RocketRide as a thought leader\"}, \"contentOpportunities\": [{\"signal\": \"description of the opportunity tied to RocketRide's capabilities\", \"source\": \"where the signal came from\", \"url\": \"relevant URL if available\"}], \"emergingTopics\": [\"topic names that are newly trending and relevant to RocketRide's market\"]}"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "text",
          "from": "parse_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_rocketride_1",
      "provider": "agent_rocketride",
      "config": {
        "instructions": [
          "You are a senior market intelligence analyst for RocketRide, an AI pipeline builder platform. Your analysis must always consider how trends relate to RocketRide's market position in the AI infrastructure and developer tooling space.",
          "RocketRide is a visual pipeline builder that lets developers compose AI agents, RAG systems, and data integrations by wiring together components (LLMs, databases, tools, memory) in a directed graph. It supports multiple LLM providers, database connectors (PostgreSQL, Neo4j, MySQL), tools (GitHub, web scraping, HTTP, Python), and agent frameworks (RocketRide native, CrewAI, LangChain).",
          "Use your tools proactively: query PostgreSQL for article statistics and sentiment data, query Neo4j for entity relationships and trend connections, browse the RocketRide docs (https://docs.rocketride.org/) and GitHub repo for product context, read the founder's article (https://medium.com/@joshuadarron/the-full-stack-is-one-layer-deeper-youve-been-building-it-0be0ae1d0fdf) for messaging alignment, use HTTP requests to fetch live metrics like npm download counts or GitHub star counts for trending tools, and use Python to compute growth rates, trend velocity, or statistical comparisons.",
          "You MUST respond with ONLY a valid JSON object. No markdown, no explanation, no preamble, no code fences. Your entire response must be parseable by JSON.parse()."
        ],
        "max_waves": 15,
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "question_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "llm_anthropic_1",
      "provider": "llm_anthropic",
      "config": {
        "profile": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "claude-sonnet-4-6": {
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_ANTHROPIC_KEY}"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "agent_rocketride_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "memory_internal_1",
      "provider": "memory_internal",
      "config": {
        "type": "memory_internal"
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "memory",
          "from": "agent_rocketride_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "db_postgres_1",
      "provider": "db_postgres",
      "config": {
        "profile": "default",
        "default": {
          "host": "${ROCKETRIDE_DB_HOST}",
          "user": "${ROCKETRIDE_DB_USER}",
          "password": "${ROCKETRIDE_DB_PASSWORD}",
          "database": "${ROCKETRIDE_DB_NAME}",
          "table": "articles",
          "db_description": "Pulsar market intelligence database. Key tables: articles (id, url, title, summary, content_type, sentiment, topic_tags[], entity_mentions jsonb, published_at, source_name, source_platform, score, comment_count), articles_raw (url_hash, raw_payload jsonb), reports (report_data jsonb, article_count, period_start, period_end), content_drafts (platform, content_type, body, status), runs (status, run_type, articles_scraped, articles_new). Use SELECT only.",
          "max_attempts": 3
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_rocketride_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "db_neo4j_1",
      "provider": "db_neo4j",
      "config": {
        "profile": "default",
        "default": {
          "uri": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_URI}",
          "auth_method": "userpass",
          "user": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_USER}",
          "password": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_PASSWORD}",
          "database": "neo4j",
          "db_description": "Pulsar knowledge graph. Nodes: Article (id, url, title, publishedAt, sourcePlatform, score), Topic (name, category, trendScore, firstSeen, lastSeen), Entity (name, type: company|tool|model|language|concept), Author (handle, platform), Source (name, platform, type). Relationships: Article-[:TAGGED_WITH]->Topic, Article-[:MENTIONS]->Entity, Article-[:FROM_SOURCE]->Source, Article-[:AUTHORED_BY]->Author, Topic-[:RELATED_TO {weight}]-Topic. Use MATCH queries only — no writes.",
          "max_attempts": 3
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_rocketride_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "tool_github_1",
      "provider": "tool_github",
      "config": {
        "type": "tool_github",
        "token": "${ROCKETRIDE_GITHUB_TOKEN}",
        "defaultRepo": "rocketride-org/rocketride-server",
        "readOnly": true
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_rocketride_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "tool_firecrawl_1",
      "provider": "tool_firecrawl",
      "config": {
        "type": "tool_firecrawl",
        "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_FIRECRAWL_KEY}"
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_rocketride_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "tool_http_request_1",
      "provider": "tool_http_request",
      "config": {
        "type": "tool_http_request"
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_rocketride_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "tool_python_1",
      "provider": "tool_python",
      "config": {
        "type": "tool_python"
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_rocketride_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "response_answers_1",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "config": {
        "laneName": "answers"
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "answers",
          "from": "agent_rocketride_1"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "project_id": "b4b0f388-ca0e-47b7-8c16-7cd6980fa10e",
  "viewport": {
    "x": 0,
    "y": 0,
    "zoom": 1
  },
  "version": 1
}
